Description: This is a 2005 Dean Evo Noir S3. These were endorsed and played by Trent Reznor of Nine Inch Nails back in the mid 2000’s.  Made in South Korea, these are good solid guitars that look and sound amazing. This guitar has a few nicks and dings, nothing above normal. It has some fretwear, again normal.  The paint is such a high gloss black, that every piece of dust or smudge shows in the pics. It is a very nice guitar. Selling as is. Item will be professionally packed, insured and shipped.  The following was copied from the internet: Trent Reznor's choice! Famous industrial musician Trent Reznor of Nine Inch Nails has recently become a Dean Guitars endorsee, this model guitar is the one that Trent uses while on tour with NIN! Dean's trademark model, the EVO is a perfect blend of vintage design, old world craftsmanship and decades of guitar building technology! The Dean EVO is truly the "Evolution of Guitar Design" at its finest. With a deep dished, carved, ultra thick flame maple top on a select Honduras mahogany body, the EVO achieves incredible sustain and astonishing tones. The EVO also features a neck joined at the body with Dean's exclusive angular neck joint. This neck joint was specially designed to attain the optimum in playability and ultimate resonance. Dean Evo Noir with S3 Headstock Features: Arched Maple Top Mahogany Body 24-3/4" Scale & 1-11/16" Nut Grover Tuners Triple Black Hardware Dean Humbucker Pickups Tune-O-Matic Bridge Set Mahogany Neck Rosewood Fingerboard 22 Frets
Title: Dean EVO Noir S3 NIN Trent Reznor 2005 Mahagony Set Neck MIK
ConditionDescription: In good working and cosmetic condition. Made in Korea. These are becoming rare.
